programme.title: Discovering Halki
programme.desc: In the south-eastern corner of the Aegean, west of Rhodes, there is a cozy island, a truly untouched gem of the Dodecanese. It is the realm of rock and absolute peace; an island with great nautical tradition and proud islanders with an innate warmth. If you are looking for a hidden paradise on earth, then you have found the right place. Greece is home to a small island called Halki. Majestic and mystical; ethereal; elegant yet unpolished; and truly authentic. In this episode we will visit Halki's capital, Emborio and we will explore, with captain George, all the natural hidden treasures of the island. Here we will discover deep caves, bask on Trahia and Kania beach, and explore Alimia islet. We will visit an abandoned village, learning more about its rich history, and scuba dive down to the sea floor to discover a mythical shipwreck.

programme.title: Inside Superyachts
programme.desc: Speed is the name of the game in this episode as we visit Dutch shipyard Heesen Yachts, renowned builder of recording breaking, fast, lightweight aluminium superyachts. We talk to naval architects "Omega" and we get an onboard look at the racing colour design of M/Y Aurelia, designed by Bannenberg & Rowell. Finally, no yacht would be complete without the latest technology and fastest onboard gadgets. We discover just what's hot on a yacht with the most sought-after tech and AV firm, IdeaWorks.

programme.title: Ciuri Ciuri
programme.desc: Sicily, the largest Mediterranean island and just off the "toe" of Italy's "boot" is the destination chosen this time by our Nautical Hosts Andi and Chelsey as they head to the South of Italy to meet up with renowned Sicilian sailors. Its rich history is not only reflected in their cuisine and culture, but also on their sailing techniques that balance tradition with modern skills. They will discover the coastlines near Palermo to learn how to tack and jibe and of course will try the delicious Sicilian cuisine. Join Andi and Chelsey on their journey around Sicily learning about sailing and tasting traditional dishes in Ciuri Ciuri, exclusive on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: The Voyage of Ghibellina
programme.desc: We set out to sail under the hot July sun and brilliant blue skies of Viareggio, a Tuscan port town best known for its long-standing tradition of shipbulding. The journey on board the Ghibellina will take us along the coast of central Italy, guiding us through the various sea passages of the area. Sit down, relax and get on board the Ghibellina with us!

programme.title: The Voyage of Ghibellina
programme.desc: In this episode, we will visit the Sicilian archipelago: the Aeolian islands. We dive into its beautiful landsdcape, villages of small white buildings and lush vegetation. These seven small islands are home to two active volcanos, Vulcano and Stromboli, and the reefs testify the many geological upheavals they have suffered. Enjoy the breathtaking sunrise as we leave the island of Stromboli.

programme.title: Jump on Board
programme.desc: In this episode of Jump on Board, Cindy, Caitlin and Linda sail from Ithaca to Cephalonia, the largest of the Ionian Islands in Western Greece and home to our captain, Marcos. The girls get divided like the semi sweet water that runs throughout the island's caves - half sweet, half salt. In the end, it's Marcos who gets the largest dose of sweet from one of the ladies. Curious to see how it goes? Jump on board with us to find out!

programme.title: Sail-Ho
programme.desc: Welcome to the third season of Sail-Ho Croatia! We have already set sail around the most beautiful and interesting parts of the Croatian coastline, and this time we wanted to go a bit further! In this episode, we'll introduce you to the beauties of Cavtat and Konavle and will visit the unmissable treasure of the region: the pearl of the Adriatic, Dubrovnik.

programme.title: Sail-Ho
programme.desc: In today's episode, we're taking you to the beautiful island of Korcula, a heaven for sailors in search for perfect bays, clear waters, exquisite wine and a mouthwatering local gastronomy. After visiting Korcula, we will pay a visit to an interesting small Dalmatian town that seems to be carved in a rock and was a known spot for notorious pirates.

programme.title: Ocean Safari: South Africa
programme.desc: The Durban port is the biggest container port in the Southern Hemisphere. Enclosed in a bay, it is capable of admitting the largest vessels, it is a compulsory Pilotage Port and for this reason controlling the port is intricate. Durban made history by announcing the first ever female marine pilots. Andi is in the Durban visiting Boni Mbambo, one of pioneers in the maritime industry.

programme.title: Ocean Safari: South Africa
programme.desc: It's back to Cape Town to meet up with two board riders. Tammy Robarts has just returned from the ISA World Surfing Games where she represented South Africa in stand up Paddle boarding. The winds in Cape Town have picked up and its time to meet with Luke Mc Gillewie, South Africa's top kite surfer.
